movies.title: Inside Llewyn Davis
movies.plot: In Greenwich Village in the early 1960s, gifted but volatile folk musician Llewyn Davis struggles with money, relationships, and his uncertain future following the suicide of his singing partner.
movies.awards: Nominated for 2 Oscars. Another 47 wins & 170 nominations.

events.title: Llewyn Davis sells a novelty song for $200

movies.title: Bastille Day
movies.plot: Michael Mason is an American pickpocket living in Paris who finds himself hunted by the CIA when he steals a bag that contains more than just a wallet. Sean Briar, the field agent on the case, soon realises that Michael is just a pawn in a much bigger game and is also his best asset to uncover a large-scale conspiracy.
